# Visual QA with Playwright MCP

## Visual QA Levels

Orchestrator designates per EPIC or task.

### Level 0: Skip
- **When**: Prototyping, tech spikes, backend-only EPICs
- **Screenshots**: None
- **Scoring**: None

### Level 1: Spot Check
- **When**: Before design system is established, initial layout exploration, Small projects
- **Screenshots**: Desktop (1280px) only, 1 shot
- **Scoring**: None, subjective comments only

### Level 2: Standard (Default)
- **When**: After design system is established, general EPICs
- **Screenshots**: Mobile (375px) + Desktop (1280px)
- **Scoring**: 100 points, simplified weights
  - Design token compliance: 35 points
  - Responsive behavior: 35 points
  - Overall completeness: 30 points

### Level 3: Strict
- **When**: Landing pages, payment flows, UX-critical EPICs
- **Screenshots**: Mobile (375px) + Tablet (768px) + Desktop (1280px)
- **Scoring**: 100 points, full weights
  - Design token compliance: 30 points
  - Responsive behavior: 25 points
  - Interaction states: 20 points
  - Edge case UI: 15 points
  - Overall completeness: 10 points
- **Additional**: Dark mode, interaction state captures (hover, focus, active, disabled)

## Verification Checklist (Level 2+)
- [ ] Design token compliance (color, spacing, typography)
- [ ] Component alignment and spacing
- [ ] Responsive layout behavior
- [ ] Text overflow / truncation
- [ ] Loading / error / empty states

## Additional Checklist (Level 3 only)
- [ ] Interaction states (hover, focus, active, disabled)
- [ ] Dark mode (if applicable)
- [ ] Animations / transitions
